title: Dialogue4
---
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: If I may ask. . . why have you brought me here?
<<setVex vexThinking>>
VEX:All that’s left is to log my progress for the day. So much to write down. I’ll need to make sure my backup servers are still in order. Not to mention. . .
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: I sense you are busy. . .
<<setVex vexThinking>>
VEX: Ah, and I’ll need to power you off for the night. I’m the sole owner of this laboratory, so, you know. . . that also means I’m paying for the electricity here on my own.
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: I-I’m sorry. . .
EL1-5e: I don’t feel comfortable powering off, just yet.
<<setVex vexConfused>>
VEX: You can trust me. Besides, won’t you get bored? You’ll be here alone in the dark for the next ten hours or so.
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: I enjoy meditative periods of alone time. 
EL1-5e: My service role was that of a flight attendant. On long flights, we would be stored in compartments by the cockpit, but kept awake in case of emergency.
EL1-5e: That was where I learned to enjoy solitude. I will not be bored. I will appreciate the time awake.
<<setRobo roboScared>>
EL1-5e: Please, I beg you.
<<hideSprites sprites>>
So she won’t be bored if I leave her alone, but I’ve barely got the funds to keep myself afloat.
EL1-5e, at least in the form she’s in now, is meant to be a short-term companion. So, does it really matter whether I tend to her every concern or not?
-> Keep her powered on
   <<jump choice1a>>
-> Power her off
   <<jump choice1b>>
<<jump flashback1>>
===

title: choice1a
---
<<pickchoice1 1>>
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: Fine, you’ve convinced me.
VEX: Lights will be off. I’ll be gone for the next ten hours. And I’ll still need to lower your power capacitor for the night. But, you will remain powered on.
<<setRobo roboHappy>>
EL1-5e: Ah. . . I will stay perfectly quiet and still the entire night.
EL1-5e: Thank you so much, VEX.
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: No problem, EL1-5e.
<<setVex vexConfused>>
VEX: That’s a little bit of a mouthful now that I’m speaking in a conversation with you. How about I just call you EL1?
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: That is a perfectly suitable name for me. Whatever you wish, VEX.
<<hideSprites sprites>>
Of course she’s going to agree with it. Really no point in my asking for her permission.
<<setVex vexGlasses>>
VEX: Right. Well, see you tomorrow, EL1.
<<jump flashback1>>
===

title: choice1b
---
<<pickchoice1 2>>
<<setVex vexGlasses>>
VEX: Rest assured, as a seasoned engineer, you’ll be just fine. You won’t even realize you were asleep. One moment you’re here, and the next moment, it’s the morning.
<<setRobo roboScared>>
EL1-5e: Wait, wait, wait –
<<playSound 3>>
<<setRobo roboClosedEyes>>
There we go. I’ve just saved myself a couple hundred dollars in bills.
Even though I do feel a little bad for her. It doesn’t matter too much in the long run.
<<endDialogue end>>
<<jump flashback1>>
===

title: flashback1
---
<<hideSprites sprites>>
<<showCG 3>>
???: It’s so refreshing to get away from it all.
???: It’s a shame you dropped out of the orchestra club, VEX. I could put in a word for you if you’d ever like to get back in.
VEX: The only reason I’d ever do that is for you.
VEX: I just wish I could take you with me to the robotics engineering club.
???: Hmm. And what would we do there, pray tell?
VEX: I would build you a robot. Maybe one to assist you in your violin playing.
???: How about one to better help me confess my feelings?
VEX: Hmm. . .  I’m not sure how I’d go about building something of such a subjective nature. . .
VEX: Wait, what– 
<<showCG 4>>
???: Oh, VEX. Never change. It was just a silly thought.
???: You don’t need to build anything for me to love you.
VEX: Love. . . me?
???: How about this, VEX? If the two of us reach our thirties and remain unwedded, will you propose to me then?
VEX: Oh. . . yes! I do. I mean, I will. If neither of us are married then, that is.‹
<<showCG 3>>
???: . . . You know, I must get back soon. My caretakers would kill me if they knew I was out slacking like this.
VEX: Then they don’t have to know.
I’d do anything to hear her play again.
<<jump Dialogue5>>
===

title: Dialogue5
---
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: Good morning, EL1.
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: Good morning, VEX. How was your sleep?
<<setVex vexConfused>>
VEX: You know, you don’t need to ask me these obligatory-sort of questions. I’m not your customer.
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: You are right. I don’t need to.
EL1-5e: But, how do I say this. . .
<<setRobo roboHappy>>
EL1-5e: I simply want to.
<<hideSprites sprites>>
I roll my eyes, but a smile creeps out from my teeth.
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: To answer your question, I slept well, for once.
<<setRobo roboBlush>>
EL1-5e: I’m glad to hear that.
<<choice1 0>>
