title: Dialogue6
---
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: Alright, it’s time for daily calibration. You know the drill. Please remain still, and let me know if...
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: If I feel discomfort, I know. You could never make me feel uncomfortable, VEX.
<<setVex vexConfused>>
VEX: But you do feel discomfort from time to time, yes?
<<setRobo roboScared>>
EL1-5e: I do.
EL1-5e: I once had a passenger on a flight attempt to grab me by the waist to get my attention.
<<setVex vexThinking>>
VEX: Oh, no? How did that end?
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: Well, my protocol was programmed to respond very strictly to any act of violence during flights.
<<setRobo roboBlush>>
EL1-5e: I turned around and. . . oh, it’s embarrassing to recall. I feel my internal systems warming up even trying to speak of it.
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: I can tell. Ehe, please, I’m intrigued.
<<setRobo roboBlush>>
EL1-5e: Well. . .
EL1-5e: I turned around and disarmed him, breaking his wrist in the process.
EL1-5e: It turned out that all he was holding was an empty cup of ice, and he just wanted a refill on his drink...
EL1-5e: My supervisors were very angry with me. As were his lawyers with the flight company, and with ASCO.
<<setVex vexSurprised>>
VEX: Oh my god.
VEX: That’s. . . hahaha. Ahahaha.
<<setRobo roboBlush>>
EL1-5e: Don’t laugh! It isn’t funny.
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: Then why are you smiling?
VEX: What drink did he even want, anyway?
<<setRobo roboBlush>>
EL1-5e: A Bloody Mary with Irish cream. . .
<<setVex vexTired>>
VEX: You can’t be serious.
