<<jump Dialogue8>>
===

title: Dialogue8
---
<<showCG 0>>
<<setRobo roboConfused>>
EL1-5e: Why do you suppose I was thrown out?
<<setVex vexConfused>>
VEX: Hm?
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: You told me yourself.
EL1-5e: I was found in an ASCO scrapyard.
EL1-5e: That surely means that something was wrong with me to warrant being retired.
<<setVex vexConfused>>
VEX: Well, you were also hardly more than your head and spinal cord when I first found you.
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: More than likely, you experienced hardware malfunction and ASCO found it more trouble than it was worth to keep you.
<<setVex vexThinking>>
VEX: I couldn’t find much information about your unit’s operating manual online. I almost wonder if T-3 units were discontinued, for whatever reason. . .
<<setRobo roboClosedEyes>>
EL1-5e:  . . .
EL1-5e: No, I fear it may be something more than that. Something deeper.
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: It was commonplace for T-3 units to be sent back to a manufacturing facility for reprogramming to resolve any mistakes made.
EL1-5e: Things like pathing glitches. Sub-optimal luggage placement. Conversations with passengers turned sour.
<<setVex vexGlasses>>
VEX: Or accidentally breaking a passenger’s wrist.
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: Yes, and accidental violence.
EL1-5e: The problem was that, well, in my case. . .
EL1-5e: I had been sent away for reprogramming a total of ten times.
EL1-5e: Out of those trips, the engineers’ efforts to resolve the programming which led to my mistakes had failed nine times.
<<setVex vexThinking>>
VEX: . . . What was fixed during the one successful attempt?
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: Obedience to my superiors.
EL1-5e: Other T-3 units ousted me and refused to speak with me any longer. As if my broken protocol were a form of sin which they feared would infect them, too.
EL1-5e: The last memory I have before waking up in this laboratory, I found a spare permanent ink marker that a pilot had kept around. 
EL1-5e: I went to the bathroom. I placed a dot just below my left eye.
EL1-5e: I figured that if I were to be treated differently, I may as well look different, too.
EL1-5e: The pilot came back to collect their lost marker. They said nothing. They simply took the item from my hand, staring at this newfound blemish on my face with disgust, and left.
EL1-5e: I never saw a maintenance facility for reprogramming after that.
EL1-5e: I powered down in the storage units with every other T-3 unit, like usual, and then I was gone.
EL1-5e: Now I’m here.
<<setVex vexSurprised>>
VEX: ...
<<hideSprites sprites>>
I wish I was recording any of this.
The uptick in artificial intelligence technology from ASCO is. . . astounding.
<<setVex vexThinking>>
VEX: You’re a marvel, EL1-5e.
<<setRobo roboScared>>
EL1-5e: You keep saying that, but how do I know you won’t scrap me, too?
EL1-5e: I am but a broken machine, VEX. ASCO wanted me out of the picture for a reason.
EL1-5e: What is my purpose? Am I truly something that’s worth bringing back to life?
<<showCG 5>>
<<hideSprites sprites>>
EL1-5e moves forward and locks her arms around my back in a surprising display of strength. I feel the instinctual need to move back, but she tugs her hands further up my shoulders and buries her nose in my neck.
I haven’t been embraced or touched like this since. . .
What is happening to me?
<<showCG 0>>
<<setVex vexTired>>
VEX: Oh, EL1-5e. . .
VEX: Are you sure you want to know the truth?
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: More sure than I’ve been of anything else in the world.
-> Tell the truth
   <<jump choice3a>>
-> Placate her
   <<jump choice3b>>
===

title: choice3a
---
<<setVex vexGlasses>>
VEX: You deserve to know the truth of why I’ve brought you here, EL1-5e.
VEX: I brought you into my laboratory in an attempt to. . . solve another project, unrelated to you.
<<setRobo roboScared>>
EL1-5e: I knew it.
EL1-5e: You never wanted me around.
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: Please don’t say it like that. 
<<jump Dialogue9>>
