<<setVex vexGlasses>>
VEX: Please don’t feel the need to worry about this.
VEX: I know you have been burned in the past. Trust that I am not like them.
<<setRobo roboBlackEyes>>
EL1-5e: . . .
EL1-5e: Lies. 
<<jump Dialogue9>>
===

title: Dialogue9
---
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: ELISE.
<<setVex vexSurprised>>
VEX: . . .? 
VEX: How do you know that name?
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: I have seen the notes you keep in your files when you think I’m not looking. I’ve seen you write about her many times before.
EL1-5e: She was a renowned violinist, gathering audiences from across the nation.
<<setVex vexConfused>>
VEX: How do you know about her?
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: I have flown with quite a few passengers on their ways to see her performances.
EL1-5e: The last I had heard of her, she had been forced to retire early due to a medical condition.
EL1-5e: You’re trying to save her, aren’t you?
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: . . . Indeed, I am.
<<setRobo roboSurprised>>
EL1-5e: But it is illegal to extract and upload human minds outside of their bodies. 
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: Why do you think I’m here all alone?
VEX: Why do you think I work so hard, day in and day out?
<<setVex vexGlasses>>
VEX: I have a loved one to save, consequences be damned.
VEX: To be honest, I never intended to meet you in this way. In fact, I never knew that your personality and memories were still intact when I first collected you up.
VEX: Nor that your sentience could even be this advanced.
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: Suppose that’s how it is when you’re forced to flee from the government for conducting unethical scientific research.
VEX: You tend to miss what goes on in the world.
<<setRobo roboScared>>
EL1-5e: . . . . . . . . . . .
EL1-5e: So, you had always planned to fix my body in order to eventually house ELISE’s consciousness.
EL1-5e: But you didn’t realize that. . . that I would still be “in here.”
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: I’m happy that I’ve met you, EL1-5e. You’ve been wonderful company for me these last few months.
<<setRobo roboScared>>
EL1-5e: Will I even. . . still be around? Will I still be "me"?
<<setVex vexGlasses>>
VEX: . . . . . . .
VEX: I’m afraid that your unit does not contain enough storage for “you,” no. 
<<setRobo roboScared>>
EL1-5e: What is your relationship to ELISE, VEX?
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: You don’t need to know that.
<<setRobo roboWhiteEyes>>
EL1-5e: None of it matters if I’m just going to be used as her replacement in the end, does it?
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: Please don’t think of it that way.
VEX: Listen. It’s time that I head out for the night, EL1-5e. We will discuss more on the topic later.
<<setRobo roboScared>>
EL1-5e: . . . please, power me off for the night, VEX.
EL1-5e: I would prefer to dream tonight than to remain in my own thoughts.
<<endDialogue end>>
<<jump flashback2>>
===

title: flashback2
---
<<hideSprites sprites>>
<<showCG 6>>
Years passed, and ELISE and I fell out of contact.
She continued her orchestral legacy, becoming one of the most prolific violinists in the nation.
She graduated the stage with thousands of hands erupting into a crescendo that drowned out the sounds of her gratitudes.
I left the stage with a simple nod, and the hope that I wouldn’t fall as I descended the stairs down.
Years passed. Our paths diverged, and we experienced the world in two entirely different ways.
Her condition worsened, yet she continued to play the violin, each performance becoming more and more cumbersome for her.
I found an interest in the more unsavory parts of robotics. This was deemed unacceptable by the law –
– therefore, by ELISE.
<<showCG 7>>
ELISE: VEX, what are you doing here?
VEX: Let me help you. You don’t need to end your legacy here, ELISE.
VEX: I could use my knowledge to build you a new body.
VEX: You could continue playing. You could walk on your own two feet again.
ELISE: VEX. . . we’ve had this conversation again and again.
ELISE: My life is nothing but constant pain and being taken care of as it is.
ELISE: You may not understand, but I love my body.
ELISE: This is what I’ve been given. The time I have left is mine.
ELISE: And after it’s all over, I just want to rest.
VEX: No, no, I can’t accept that.
VEX: Remember our promise? You could have everything you want. We could have everything we want.
ELISE: You’re making this more painful for me. I’ll only say it once.
ELISE: Leave.
Just as I predicted – it wasn’t long before ELISE’s fragile body could no longer withstand the rot that was spreading within it.
She was 30 years old, with no lover, no children, and no family. All she had left was me.
I’m the only person who can care for ELISE in a way that matters.
<<showCG 8>>
VEX: I’ll never leave you, ELISE.
VEX: You may not understand it now, but I hope you will the next time you see me, no matter what form you’re in.
<<endDialogue end>>
===

title: Dialogue10
---
<<showCG 0>>
<<setVex vexTired>>
VEX: . . . Recording: Day 223. I’ve been making significant jumps in progress in the time since I last spoke with EL1-5e.
VEX: I haven’t needed to power her on for quite some time. An awake mind is not necessary for the upgrades I’ve been doing.
VEX: . . . But today is different. Today marks whether I’ve succeeded in my career, in my life. . .
<<setVex vexGlasses>>
VEX: . . . or failed.
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: I will need to power EL1-5e on in order to ensure that the mind-body connection is still intact.
VEX: Afterwards, I will need to upload ELISE’s memories. . .
VEX: . . . which will override any memories and personality currently in the T-3 unit.
VEX: If all goes well, then. . . then I may get to speak with ELISE, by the end of the day, today.
VEX: I feel so ecstatic that I must concentrate to keep my hands from shaking.
<<setVex vexGlasses>>
VEX: But at the same time, I am. . . 
VEX: Terrified of the outcome.
VEX: . . . . . . . . .
VEX: I’ve got to power on EL1-5e.
VEX: Good morning, EL1-5e.
<<setRobo roboScared>>
EL1-5e:. . . . . Good morning.
<<setRobo roboSuprised>>
EL1-5e: Am I. . . still needed, at this point in time?
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX: Yes, EL1. You are still ‘alive.’ I’m going to need you awake for today.
<<setRobo roboNeutral>>
EL1-5e: Why?
<<setVex vexNeutral>>
VEX:I’m going to need feedback from a live specimen. Not to worry, EL1. If all goes well, you won’t remember any of this by the end of the day.
<<setRobo roboScared>>
EL1-5e: Are. . . you going to erase my memories?
<<setVex vexThinking>>
VEX: Well, there will be no memories to erase, so to speak.
<<hideSprites sprites>>
EL1 fights against the constraints of the holding skeleton I’ve got her attached to. There’s so much more movement in her shoulders; more harmony in the swell of her body as her hips jut out in an attempt to find space to move.
There is none. I made sure to secure the holding skeleton in anticipation of the body’s increased movement control.
<<setRobo roboScared>>
EL1-5e: . . . Why, yes. Of course. L-let. . . let me know what I can do. . . to help.
<<hideSprites sprites>>
Of course I know what I’m doing to her. It’s almost cruel, in a way, to watch an animal fight against its trap while the hunter picks it apart to be eaten.
But I must.
I have no other choice.
<<setVex vexGlasses>>
VEX: Right. Shall we get started?

===

title:Maintenance13
---
EL1-5e: You seem chipper, today.
VEX: Ah, do I? Call it a ‘nervous excitement,’ then.
EL1-5e: Nervous because. . . because you aren’t sure if you will succeed?
VEX: No, more like. . .
VEX: . . . nervous to see how ELISE will react.
VEX: I don’t think she will be too happy when she wakes up.
EL1-5e: . . . . .
<<endDialogue end>>
